CHRISTMAS PUPPY CHOW ✨ The girls and I made our Mimi’s infamous puppy chow (see below for the key ingredient) and made it Christmasy by adding ande’s mint chips and m&ms. What would you add!?

INGREDIENTS:
- 2 sticks butter
- 3/4 cup creamy peanut butter 
- 12 oz bag chocolate chips 
- 12 oz box crispex cereal (best brand to use)
- 1 bag powdered sugar (KEY INGREDIENT - use the WHOLE bag!!)

HOW TO:
1. Melt peanut butter, butter and chocolate in a deep pot
2. Add Crispex to pot, put lid on and shake
3. Pour mixture in double lined paper bag, add powdered sugar, and shake! (We usually do this step outside in case the powdered sugar escapes)
4. Add your chocolate candy of choice!

HOMEMADE CINNAMON CANDY RECIPE:

INGREDIENTS:
• 2 C sugar
• 1 C white corn syrup 
• 1/2 C water
• 3/4 tsp red food coloring 
• 1.5 tsp cinnamon oil 

 INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Heat sugar, corn syrup and water over medium heat until it reaches 295 degrees F.
2. Stir in food coloring and oil of cinnamon.
3. Pour I to a foil-lined pan.
4. As it starts to cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar for easier handling.
5. When the mixture has cooled, break apart into bite-sized pieces with your hands. 

Enjoy!!
